#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "There are several pieces of additional software that, while not required, will aid in the overall use of NvChad. The sections below will walk you through that software and its uses.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "RipGrep"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "`ripgrep` is a line-oriented search tool that recursively searches the current directory for a _regex_ (regular expression) pattern. By default, _ripgrep_ respects the rules of _gitignore_ and automatically skips hidden files/directories and binaries. Ripgrep offers excellent support on Windows, macOS and Linux, with binaries available for each release.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install RipGrep from EPEL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "In both Rocky Linux 8 and 9, you can install RipGrep from the EPEL. To do this, install the `epel-release,` upgrade the system, and then install `ripgrep.`:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo dnf install -y epel-release\n"
"sudo dnf upgrade\n"
"sudo dnf install ripgrep\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install RipGrep using `cargo`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ripgrep is software written in _Rust_ and is installable with the `cargo` utility. Note, however, that `cargo` is not installed by the default installation of _rust_ so you have to install it explicitly. If you run into errors using this method, revert back to installing from the EPEL.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install rust cargo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the necessary software is installed, we can install `ripgrep` with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "cargo install ripgrep\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "The installation will save the `rg` executable in the `~/.cargo/bin` folder which is outside the PATH, to use it at the user level we will link it to `~/.local/bin/`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "ln -s ~/.cargo/bin/rg ~/.local/bin/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "RipGrep Verification"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "At this point we can check that everything is okay with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rg --version\n"
"ripgrep 13.0.0\n"
"-SIMD -AVX (compiled)\n"
"+SIMD +AVX (runtime)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "RipGrep is needed for recursive searches with `:Telescope`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Lazygit"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "[LazyGit](https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit) is an ncurses-style interface that allows you to perform all `git` operations in a more user-friendly way. It is required by the _lazygit.nvim_ plugin. This plugin makes it possible to use LazyGit directly from NvChad, it opens a floating window from where you can perform all operations on your repositories, thus allowing you to make all changes to the _git repository_ without leaving the editor.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "To install it we can use the repository for Fedora. On Rocky Linux 9 it works perfectly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo dnf copr enable atim/lazygit -y\n"
"sudo dnf install lazygit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once installed we open a terminal and type the command `lazygit` and an interface similar to this will appear: \n"
msgstr ""

